Narrative-Based Learning (ASU Cycle)
ASU = Assess → Story → Update
The WVM learns through processing cultural narratives, not abstract data points.

Learning Cycle:
text
1. SELECT STORY
   ↓
2. EXPERIENCE (Read/Parse narrative)
   ↓
3. INTERPRET (Understand cultural implications)
   ↓
4. CONCLUDE (Draw worldview implications)
   ↓
5. RE-ASSESS (Answer 5 dimension questions)
   ↓
6. UPDATE BUFFER (New worldview positions)
   ↓
7. COMPUTE VARIANCE (Measure dissonance)
   ↓
8. TRIGGER DRM (If dissonance high)
